The Delta Central 2023 (DC-23) lobby group has paid visit to Hon. Reuben Izeze, member representing Ughelli South Constituency in the Delta State House of Assembly who was recently attacked by unknown gunmen at Ekpan, Uvwie Local Government Area of Delta State. Dr. Chris Oharisi, National Secretary of DC-23 who spoke on behalf of the group during the visit, stated that they were there on the orders of the National Chairman, Chief Senator Ighoyota Amori to rejoice with him for God to had saved him from the hands of gunmen who shot at him. Oharisi expressed appreciation to God Almighty for saving the life of the lawmaker who is also the First Vice National Chairman of Delta Central 2023 lobby group. Buhari’s Aide Backs Wike On War Against Bunkering In Rivers 2023: DPV Reaffirms Commitment To Okowa”s Leadership “I pray against untimely death of DC-23 executives and members. We meant well for Urhobos and Deltans as such God will always be our shield against the arrows of ungrateful people, armed robbers, gunmen, bandits and others”, he added. In his response, Hon. Reuben Izeze expressed appreciation to the executives and members of DC-23 for the visit. The lawmaker who narrated how he was shot and left for dead by the gunmen, said, he sees the visit as celebration and victory over untimely death. Executives and members of DC-23 that went for the visit included Dr. Chris Oharisi, National Secretary, Rt. Hon. Chief Sunday Apah, Assistant National Publicity Secretary, Chief George Osikorobia, National Auditor, Chief Pius Ovbije, Assistant National, Abraham Whisky, National Provost, Hon. Elohor Uwhobe, Assistant National Women Leader, Chief Mrs. Jegede, Engr. Eric Osiobe, Chief Michael Akpobasa, Chief David Ejukonemu, Mr. Kennedy Atevure, Chief Bestman Itive and Mr. Onojovwo.